From: PS4 Linux Port <ps4linux@localhost>
Date: Tue, 14 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ps4: bpcie-icc: Fix ioread32/iowrite32 pointer type errors

The ioread32() and iowrite32() functions expect void __iomem * pointers,
not u32 integers. This causes build errors with modern kernels that are
stricter about pointer types.

Fix by changing the addr variable type from u32 to void __iomem *.

Fixes build error:
  drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c:292:35: error: passing argument 1 of
  'ioread32' makes pointer from integer without a cast [-Wint-conversion]

Signed-off-by: PS4 Linux Port <ps4linux@localhost>
---
 drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c b/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c
+++ b/drivers/ps4/ps4-bpcie-icc.c
@@ -283,7 +283,7 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(bpcie_icc_cmd);
 
 static void bpcie_init_usb(struct bpcie_dev *sc, int usb_no) {
 	u32 value_to_write;
-	u32 addr;
+	void __iomem *addr;
 	u32 offset;
 
 	offset = usb_no ? 0x68 : 0x64;
